docs.lead_paragraph: Resumption of milk deliveries in the metropolitan area got off to an encouraging if somewhat belated start yesterday morning, following acceptance on Friday night of the Office of Defense Transportation's skip-a-day delivery order by officials of the Milk Wagon Drivers Union, an affiliate of the American Federation of Labor.

headline.main: MILK DELIVERIES TARDILY RESUMED; Drivers Leave Loading Plants Several Hours Behind Their Regular Schedules

docs.abstract: prevails on striking Borden Co drivers to return to work
